cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.CR

The paper explores citation relationships among publications in the computer science field, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The focus on citation networks and scholarly datasets suggests that it could belong to cs.DL (Digital Libraries) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of citation analysis also suggests that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.SD (Software Engineering). Finally, the discussion of impact and publication years suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
